==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|eng}} {{term|ἀμέθυστος||not drunk|tr=amethustos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|ἀ-||not|tr=a-|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|μεθύω||I am drunk|tr=methuō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|μέθυ||wine|tr=methu|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}. The Greeks believed that the amethyst prevented [[intoxication]].

===Noun===
'''amethyst'''  (''plural'' '''[[amethysts]]''')

# A [[transparent]] [[purple]] variety of [[quartz]], used as a [[gemstone]].
# A [[purple]] [[colour]].
#: <table><tr><td>amethyst colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#86608E" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>
# {{heraldry}} The purple [[tincture]] when [[emblazon]]ing the [[arms]] of the English [[nobility]].

